Though having been ruled since 1603 in [[Personal Union]] when [[James VI]] succeeded both the [[Union of the Crowns|English and Scottish crowns]] both countries remained separate sovereign nations states until 1706 when the [[Treaty of Union]] unified them into a single entity.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Star-Spangled Banner flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Vermont Republic.svg}} [[Vermont Republic]]<br />{{flagicon image|Hopkinson Flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| 1777\u20131791\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Star-Spangled Banner flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flag|Connecticut}}<br />{{flag|Delaware}}<br />{{flag|Georgia (U.S. state)|name=Georgia}}<br />{{flag|Maryland}}<br />{{flag|Massachusetts}}<br />{{flag|New Hampshire}}<br />{{flag|New Jersey}}<br />{{flag|New York}}<br />{{flag|North Carolina}}<br />{{flag|Pennsylvania}}<br />{{flag|Rhode Island}}<br />{{flag|South Carolina}}<br />{{flag|Virginia}}\n| 1786-1788\n| {{yes|Yes  <br /> (1788\u20131861)}}\n| [[United States Constitution]] is ratified by the [[Thirteen Colonies|Thirteen Original Colonies]], replacing the [[Articles of Confederation]] and thereby forming a Federal government, ending the individual sovereignty of the US States.\n|}\n\n===19th century===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"130\" | Proposed state\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"150\" | Components\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"70\" | Time period\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"80\" | Successful?\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"620\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the United Kingdom.svg}} [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]]\n| {{flag|Kingdom of Great Britain|1606}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Ireland}}\n| 1800\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1801\u20131922)}}\n| Most of Ireland left the union as the [[Irish Free State]] in 1922.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Gran Colombia.svg}} [[Gran Colombia]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of New Granada (1814-1816).svg}} [[United Provinces of New Granada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Bandera de Angostura (20 de noviembre de 1817).svg}} [[Second Republic of Venezuela|Venezuela]]<br />{{flagicon image|Bandera de la Provincia Libre de Guayaquil.svg}} [[Royal Audiencia of Quito|Free Province of Guayaquil]]\n| 1819\u20131830\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1819\u20131830)}}\n| \n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Bandera del Primer Imperio Mexicano.svg}} [[First Mexican Empire]]\n| {{flagicon image|Bandera del Primer Imperio Mexicano.svg}} [[Mexico]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Spain (1785\u20131873, 1875\u20131931).svg}}[[Captaincy General of Guatemala]]\n| 1821\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1821\u20131823)}}\n| [[Central America]] was annexed into the [[First Mexican Empire]]. After the dissolution of the Empire only [[Chiapas]] choose to remain part of [[Mexico]], the rest became the [[Federal Republic of Central America]]. \nCosta Rica in particular was split between inner factions in favor and against the annexation ending in a [[Ochomogo War|Civil War]]. The pro-Mexican provinces declared membership but was not recognized by the pro-independence provinces.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Federal Republic of Central America.svg}} [[Federal Republic of Central America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Civil Flag of El Salvador.png}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Honduras (1839-1866).svg}} [[Honduras]]<br />{{flagicon image|Zentralamerikanische Konf\u00f6deration 1823-1824.svg}} [[Nicaragua]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Guatemala (1825-1838).svg}} [[Guatemala]] <br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Los Altos.svg}} [[Los Altos, Central America|Los Altos]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1823-1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| 1823\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1823\u20131839)}}\n| \n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824-1840).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]<br /> {{flagicon image|Bandera de la Provincia de Guanacaste.svg}} [[Partido de Nicoya|Nicoya]]\n| 1824\n| {{yes}}\n|