ptaincy General of Puerto Rico]]<br />{{flag|Dominican Republic}}\n| 1869\u20131870\n| {{no}}\n| Proposed by [[Ram\u00f3n Emeterio Betances]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the German Empire.svg}} [[German Empire]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the German Empire.svg}} [[North German Confederation]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Bavaria (striped).svg}} [[Kingdom of Bavaria]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge K\u00f6nigreich W\u00fcrttemberg.svg}} [[Kingdom of W\u00fcrttemberg]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge Gro\u00dfherzogtum Baden (1891-1918).svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Baden]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flagge Gro\u00dfherzogtum Hessen ohne Wappen.svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Hesse]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dienstflagge Elsa\u00df-Lothringen Kaiserreich.svg}} [[Alsace-Lorraine]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Habsburg Monarchy.svg}} [[Austrian Empire]]\n| 1871\n| {{yes|Partial <br /> (1871\u20131918)}}\n| [[Unification of Germany]] (excluding Austria) after German victory over the French in the [[Franco-Prussian War]]. See also, the [[German Question]] regarding the competing ideas of \"Greater Germany\" and \"Lesser Germany\" (whether or not a united Germany should include the Austrian Empire). The matter was settled with the [[Austro-Prussian War]] in 1866, in which Prussia assumed leadership of the various minor German nation states.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria.svg}} [[Principality of Bulgaria]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria.svg}} [[Bulgaria]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Eastern Rumelia.svg}} [[East Rumelia]]\n| 1885-1886\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| After Bulgaria crushed Serbia in the [[Serbo-Bulgarian War]] of 1885, Bulgaria nearly doubled in size when [[East Rumelia]] was incorporated within its borders. Bulgaria officially annexed it from the [[Ottoman Empire]] in 1885.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Zentralamerikanische Gro\u00dfrepublik 1898.svg}} [[Greater Republic of Central America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of El Salvador (1875-1877).svg}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagi