ialist Federative Soviet Republic|Transcaucasian SFSR]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Ukrainian SSR (1919-1929).svg}} [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|Ukrainian SSR]]\n| 1922\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1922\u20131991)}}\n| [[Treaty on the Creation of the USSR]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of German Reich (1935\u20131945).svg}} [[Nazi Germany]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of German Reich (1935\u20131945).svg}} [[Nazi Germany]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Austria.svg}} [[Federal State of Austria]]\n| 1938\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1938\u20131945)}}\n| [[Anschluss]]\n|-\n| {{flag|Turkey|name=Republic of Turkey}}\n| {{flag|Turkey|name=Republic of Turkey}}<br />{{flag|Hatay State}}\n|1939\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Hatay Province|Hatay]] was a disputed territory between [[Syria]] and [[Turkey]] until 2004. Territory ceded from Syria to Turkey during the French Mandate of Syria, never formally recognized by Syria, but gave it up in 2004.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} [[Polish-Czechoslovak confederation]]\n| {{flag|First Czechoslovak Republic|name=Czechoslovak Republic}}<br />{{flag|Second Polish Republic|name=Polish Republic}}\n| 1939\u20131948\n| {{no}}\n| Proposed by [[W\u0142adys\u0142aw Sikorski]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} [[Greek-Yugoslav confederation]]\n| Strictest definition:<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Greece}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Yugoslavia}}<br />Loosest definition also includes:<br />{{flag|Albanian Kingdom}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Bulgaria}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Romania}}\n| 1942\u20131944\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of SFR Yugoslavia.svg}} [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of SFR Yugoslavia.svg}} [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Albania 1946.svg}} [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria (1971-1990).svg}} [[People's Republic of Bulgaria]]\n| 1946\u20131948\n| {{no}}\n| [[Josip Broz Tito]] came extremely close to getting Albania into accepting integration into Yugoslavia, but relations cooled in 1948 over fears that Yugoslavia only intended to use Albania for raw materials, subsequently resulting in the expulsion of Yugoslav diplomats. Yugoslav/Bulgarian negotiations fell through when Moscow attempted to force both countries into accepting Soviet control over the merge, which caused Yugoslavia to withdraw from negotiations and precipitated the [[Tito\u2013Stalin split]].\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Drapeau Junagadh vector.svg}} [[Junagadh State|Junagadh]]\n| 1947\u20131948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Annexation of Junagadh]]\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon|British Raj}}[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}<br />[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n| {{flag|India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Asafia flag of Hyderabad State.png}} [[Hyderabad State|Hyderabad]]\n| 1948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Indian annexation of Hyderabad|Annexation of Hyderabad]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada]]\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dominion of Newfoundland Red Ensign.svg}} [[Dominion of Newfoundland|Newfoundland]]\n| 1949\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Newfoundland Act]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland (1953\u20131963).svg}} [[Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland]]\n| {{flag|Nyasaland|1963}}<br />{{flag|Northern Rhodesia|1939-1953}}<br />{{flag|Southern Rhodesia}}\n| 1953\n| {{yes|Yes <br />(1953\u20131963)}}\n| A semi-independent state.\n|-\n| {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]]\n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Malta (1943-1964).svg}} [[Crown Colony of Malta]]\